# AppX Package Installer for Windows 10/11 | Modern MSIX/AppX Installer Tool

A modern, user-friendly Windows application for installing AppX and MSIX packages with a sleek drag-and-drop interface. Supports automatic dependency management, license handling, and system architecture detection.

## üè∑Ô∏è Keywords

`AppX installer` ‚Ä¢ `MSIX package installer` ‚Ä¢ `Windows package manager` ‚Ä¢ `Drag and drop installer` ‚Ä¢ `AppX bundle installer` ‚Ä¢ `Windows 10 package tool` ‚Ä¢ `Windows 11 MSIX tool` ‚Ä¢ `PowerShell package installer`

![Installation Demo](assets/AppX_Installer.gif)

## ‚ú® Features

- **Drag & Drop Interface** - Simply drag your AppX files into the application
- **Multiple Format Support** - Supports `.appx`, `.appxbundle`, `.msix`, and `.msixbundle` files
- **Smart Package Detection** - Automatically identifies dependencies, main apps, and bundles
- **Architecture Compatibility** - Checks and installs compatible packages for your system
- **Modern UI** - Beautiful gradient design with smooth animations
- **Installation Progress** - Real-time status updates during installation
- **Automatic License Handling** - Searches for and applies license files when available

## üéØ How to Use

![Usage Demo](assets/AppX_Installer_USE.gif)

1. **Launch the application**
2. **Drag and drop** your AppX package files into the main window
3. **Wait for installation** - The app will automatically install all packages
4. **Success notification** - Get confirmation when installation is complete

## üì¶ Supported File Types

| Format | Description | Type Label |
|--------|-------------|------------|
| `.appx` | Application Package | APP/DEP |
| `.appxbundle` | Bundle Package | BUNDLE |
| `.msix` | Modern Package | APP/DEP |
| `.msixbundle` | Modern Bundle | BUNDLE |

## üîß Installation Priority

The installer automatically handles package dependencies by installing in the correct order:

1. **Dependencies** (VCLibs, NET, Xaml, WinJS) - Installed first
2. **Main Applications** - Installed second
3. **Bundles** - Installed last

## üõ†Ô∏è System Requirements

- **OS**: Windows 10/11
- **Framework**: .NET Framework 4.7.2 or higher
- **PowerShell**: Windows PowerShell (built-in)
- **Privileges**: Administrator rights recommended for system-wide installation

## ‚ö° Technical Features

### Smart Installation Logic
- Uses PowerShell's `Add-AppxProvisionedPackage` for system-wide installation
- Falls back to `Add-AppxPackage` for user-specific installation
- Automatic license file detection and application

### Architecture Detection
- Automatically filters packages based on system architecture
- Prevents installation of incompatible ARM/x64 packages on x86 systems

### Error Handling
- Graceful error handling with user-friendly messages
- Cancellation support for long-running installations
- Automatic cleanup on application exit

## üé® UI States

The application features three main UI states:

1. **Empty State** - Drag & drop interface
2. **Loading State** - Installation progress with spinner animation
3. **Success State** - Completion confirmation with checkmark animation

## üöÄ Getting Started

### Prerequisites
- Visual Studio 2019 or later
- .NET Framework 4.7.2 SDK
- Windows 10 SDK

### Building from Source

```bash
git clone https://github.com/EXLOUD/AppX-Package-Installer.git
cd AppX-Package-Installer
```

Open the solution in Visual Studio and build the project.

### Running the Application

1. Build the project in Visual Studio
2. Run the executable as Administrator (recommended)
3. Drag and drop your AppX files to install

## üìã Usage Tips

- **Administrator Mode**: Run as administrator for system-wide package installation
- **Multiple Files**: You can drag multiple packages at once - they'll be installed in the correct order
- **License Files**: Place license files (`.xml`) in the same directory as your packages for automatic detection
- **Architecture**: The app automatically filters out incompatible packages based on your system architecture

## üêõ Troubleshooting

### Common Issues

**Installation Fails**
- Ensure you're running as Administrator
- Check if the package is compatible with your Windows version
- Verify the package isn't corrupted

**Drag & Drop Not Working**
- Make sure the files have the correct extensions (.appx, .msix, etc.)
- Try running the application as Administrator

**PowerShell Errors**
- Ensure PowerShell execution policy allows script execution
- Check Windows Update for the latest PowerShell version

